    Graph<T extends Object>
    A mathematical graph-theory graph object G(V,E) which contains a set V of vertices and a set E of edges. Each edge e=(v1,v2) in E connects vertex v1 to vertex v2. Here the graph vertex is referred to as a Node.
    GraphBuilder<T extends Object>
    Generic graph builder to build a graph from traversed nodes and edges. All edges will have attributes.

    Generic interface for implementations that walk an object graph, e.g. on an entity instance, via XML, or through metadata.
    GraphView<T extends Object>
    A GraphView is a read-only view on a Graph. Implementations will generally be optimized for multiple read operations (i.e., some "startup cost" but with faster operations).
    GraphVisitor<T extends Object>
    Interface for visitors which can perform logic for each node (or edge) in a graph.
